Buddemeyer in Talks to Buy London’s Riverbank Hotel, Times Says

-- B y   L i n d s a y   F o r t a d o
-- 
2011-03-06T09:42:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-06/buddemeyer-in-talks-to-buy-london-s-riverbank-hotel-times-says.html
David Buddemeyer’s  Driftwood
Hospitality Management  is in talks to buy  London ’s Riverbank
hotel from  Park Plaza Hotels Ltd. (PPH)  for 150 million pounds ($244
million), the Sunday Times reported, without saying where it got
the information.  Park Plaza is being advised by  Gerard Nolan & Partners  in
the unsolicited offer for the 396-room hotel, located across the
river from parliament, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lindsay Fortado in London at 
 lfortado@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net . 